Cregganbaun
footnotes               Cregganbaun () is a village in Mayo, Ireland.GeologyIn 2007 there were reports of a proposal by a company called Mayos Gold to open a niche tourism gold mine in Cregganbaun, and an interpretative visitor centre in Louisburgh. This re-ignited a 20 years controversy when several mining companies attempted to open commercial quantity gold mines on the side of Patrick and in the Cregganbaun/Doolough region. The principal idea was to develop a national tourism product based around a show mine, producing a small amount of gold and not a commercial mining venture().EducationCregganbaun National School is now disused and local children travel to modern schools at Killeen or Louisburgh().See also* List of towns and villages in IrelandReferencesde:CregganbaunCreagn Bnnl:Cregganbaunru:
