Edward_Borron
 religion          Edward Barnes Borron (December 6, 1820 &ndash; April 23, 1915) was a Canadian politician. He represented the electoral district of Algoma in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1878. He was a member of the Liberal Party.The son of John Arthur Borron and Mary Geddes, he was educated at Lancashire, upon Tyne and the of Edinburgh before entering work in his fathers mines in Lanarkshire. In 1842, he became general manager. Borron came to Canada in 1850, working in Michigan before becoming general manager for the Montreal Mining Companys operation at Bruce Mines. He married Marie-Edesse Fvrier dit Larame in 1854. In 1858, he returned to Scotland but came back to the Sault Ste. Marie area in 1862. From 1869 to 1873, he was crown lands agent and mining inspector for the province in the Lake Superior division. In 1879, he was named stipendiary magistrate for the northern Nipissing district. He retired to Toronto in 1904. References * * 
