Mount_Lyell
Mount Lyell can refer to:*Lyell (California), the highest point in Yosemite National Park in California, United States.*Lyell (Tasmania), a peak in Tasmania, Australia.*Lyell (Canada), a peak on the AlbertaBritish Columbia boundary.*Lyell Mining and Railway Company in Tasmania existed between 1897 and 1994.:Note - the Mountains named after Lyell were done so in the nineteenth century during the controversy about Darwins theory of evolution.
