Marysvale_Canyon
Marysvale Canyon or Sevier Canyon () runs eight miles (13 km) north from Utah to the town of Utah. It is a steep walled canyon formed by the flow of the meandering River.Points of interest in the canyon are Big Rock Candy Mountain, old mining sites, and the rail tunnels along the old Branch of the and Rio Grande Western Railroad that has been converted to a hiking/biking path.* Official Website of Marysvale Utah* Marysvale Canyon* Rock Candy Express Bike Trail* Sevier River* Historic Mining Sites* Canyon of Gold Tour
