RBM
RBM is a three-letter acronym. It refers to:*The Back Malaria (RBM) Partnership, the global framework to implement coordinated action against malaria.*bone marrow, a tissue found at the core of large bones*Based Maintenance; risk assessment software (RBM-software)*Restricted Boltzmann Machine, a type of neural network used in artificial intelligence applications*Belt Music, a San Franciscan band*Merganser, a diving duck*des Bains de Mer a group of metre gauge railways centred on Noyelles-sur-Mer in France*Bank of Malawi, a central bank in Republic of Malawi*Rotational Brownian motion*Bart Mampaey, a racing team competing in the Touring Car Championship, running the BMW Team RBM operation*Bay Minerals, a South African mining company*Bound Material*Banned Member,a member of a forum who was previously banned returning under a different handleReferencesde:RBMit:RBM
